 ('4','1','2','Cranberry Booms','1','category_image_fpo.gif','59','54','cranberry-booms','<p style=\"clear: right;\">\n<img src=\"/images/cranberry_boom_in_use.jpg\" alt=\"tbd\" style=\"display: block; float: right; margin: 0 0 20px 20px;\" />\n								4\" Diameter Flotation<br />\n								4\" Skirt Depth<br />\n								1/4\" Galvanized Chain Ballast<br />\n								Aluminum quick latch couplers with floats and stainless steel locking pins.<br />\n								Aluminum tow bridles to match up with the ends on the total boom.\n						</p>\n						<h4 style=\"color: #000; font-size: 14px;\">Recommended Section Lengths: <span class=\"normal\">50\' and 100\'</span></h4>\n						<p><strong>Recommended Use: </strong>4\" x 4\" cranberry booms are floating containment devices that corral floating cranberries on the water after harvesters have beaten the berries loose from the vines. Contained within the boom, the berries are pulled to shore at the most convenient point for recovery.  Booms allow berries on the water to be concentrated to a thickness of up to 4\" for more efficient recovery.\n</p>\n<p><a href=\"#\" title=\"\">Call or e-mail us for references.</a></p>\n						<h3><a href=\"/request_quote\" title=\"\">Request A Quote: Click here</a></h3>',null),
